3. Decides the Government of Sudan and the SPLM-North shall cooperate with AUHIP and IGAD to reach a negotiated settlement;

4. Urges Sudan and the SPLM-N to accept the tripartite proposal for humanitarian access;

5. Decides negotiations shall conclude within three months; if failed, the Secretary-General shall report to the Security Council;

6. Requests the Secretary-General to consult with the African Union, work closely with AUHIP, and report on compliance;

7. Calls upon parties to promote and protect human rights, comply with international law, and hold accountable those responsible for serious violations.
The Security Council:

8. Commends UNISFA's efforts in carrying out its mandate, expresses appreciation for the Force Commander's work and troop-contributing countries, and intends to evaluate UNISFA's mandate based on Sudan and South Sudan's compliance with this resolution and their 2011 Agreements;

9. Stresses the need to restore comprehensive, just and lasting peace between Sudan and South Sudan;

10. Decides to remain actively seized of this matter.
